---
import Image from "astro/components/Image.astro";
import breakfast from "../../images/splash/rust-lambda-breakfast.jpg";
import CheckIcon from "../icons/CheckIcon.astro";
import BuyButton from "../BuyButton.astro";
---

<section class="my-12">
  <div
    class="mt-32 mb-8 flex flex-col justify-center align-middle gap-4 items-center"
  >
    <h2
      class="text-center text-2xl font-bold sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl/line-tight bg-gradient-to-tr from-primary-alt to-primary inline-block text-transparent bg-clip-text"
    >
      Who is this book for
    </h2>
  </div>

  <div
    class="bg-card/50 text-card-foreground border border-border rounded-md p-8"
  >
    <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-8 justify-center items-center">
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 text-lg/8 max-w-lg">
        <p>
          This book is designed for cloud developers who are passionate about
          Serverless and want to build green, efficient, and cost-effective
          serverless solutions using Rust and AWS Lambda.
        </p>
        <p>
          This book assumes you have some basic understanding of the Rust
          programming language. If that's something totally new for you, we'd
          recommend you to check out the <a
            href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="nofollow noopener"
            class="underline">official Rust book</a
          > (available for FREE) first.
        </p>
        <p>
          You will also need some basic understanding of AWS and serverless. If
          you are new to AWS, we recommend you to try some of the FREE <a
            href="https://workshops.aws/categories/Lambda"
            target="_blank"
            rel="nofollow noopener"
            class="underline">Lambda workshops by AWS</a
          >.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <Image
          src={breakfast}
          width="600"
          height="400"
          alt="A breakfast table with coffee mugs, some milk, cherries, biscuits and a red coffee mocha maker."
          quality={90}
          decoding="sync"
          loading="eager"
          class="aspect-[6/4] overflow-hidden rounded-md object-cover object-center shadow-lg z-0"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col justify-center align-middle items-center mt-8">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-2xl mt-8 my-4 ml-6">
          This book is for you if:
        </h3>
        <ul class="max-w-xl space-y-1 text-xl">
          <li class="flex gap-2 items-baseline">
            <CheckIcon
              class="text-accent h-5 flex-shrink-0 translate-y-1"
            /><span
              >You are a cloud developer with a passion for Serverless</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-2 items-baseline">
            <CheckIcon
              class="text-accent h-5 flex-shrink-0 translate-y-1"
            /><span
              >You have very basic understanding of the Rust programming
              language</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-2 items-baseline">
            <CheckIcon
              class="text-accent h-5 flex-shrink-0 translate-y-1"
            /><span>You have basic knowledge of AWS and Lambda</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-2 items-baseline">
            <CheckIcon class="text-accent h-5 flex-shrink-0 translate-y-1" />
            <span
              >You are eager to build greener, efficient, and cost-effective
              serverless solutions</span
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-8 text-center">
          <BuyButton />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
